main event: A circular, yellowish-white object was observed in wavering flight for 2-5 minutes over Tipp City, Ohio on August 29, 1965.
interesting points: The object moved behind clouds and was slightly brighter than the brightest star.
The object's motion was similar to that of the Echo II satellite, which was over Dayton, Ohio at the time.
The witness observed the object moving to the northeast.
The report includes a questionnaire with additional details about the sighting, such as time, location, duration, and witness description.
The report concludes that the observed object was likely the Echo II satellite.
photographs: yes, but not included in the report
